Governor Kayode Fayemi of Ekiti State, has appointed Foluso Daramola as the new Secretary to the State Government (SSG). Fayemi made the announcement in a statement issued by his Chief Press Secretary, Mr Yinka Oyebode on Monday. The Governor also named a 39-year-old Mr Tolu Ibitola, as his new Chief of Staff. The two appointments, according to the governor, are with immediate effect. The new SSG, is a retired Permanent Secretary and member of the State Executive Council. Daramola was also, until his new appointment, the Overseer, Office of the Secretary to the State Government, a position he assumed following the resignation of Mr Biodun Oyebanji in December 2021.